<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1366,1392]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[359,434,1366,1392]" name="Russia" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[448,630,1366,1392]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[649,793,1366,1393]" name="South Korea" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">South Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,457,1402,1429]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1437,1294,1897]" box="[199,457,1402,1429]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1402,1428]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Host plant</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1437,1294,1897]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1438,1464]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was described from Primorskij Kraj by 
<bibRefCitation author="Benes, K." box="[907,1057,1438,1464]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="298 - 314" refId="ref72854" refString="Benes, K. (1974) The Siberian species of Pamphilius Latr., related to P. histrio Latr. (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 71, 298 - 314." type="journal article" year="1974">Beneš (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and later recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1333,1401,1439,1465]" name="South Korea" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Korea</collectingCountry>
by Shinohara (1993), who also described a Japanese subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1993" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" box="[851,1370,1474,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zhelochovtsevi" subSpecies="nipponicus">
<emphasis box="[851,1174,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. zhelochovtsevi nipponicus</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1993
</taxonomicName>
, from Honshu. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[253,450,1510,1537]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="241 - 258" refId="ref79811" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2015) To the sawfly fauna (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of southern Kuriles. A. I. Kurentsov's Annual Memorial Meetings, Issue XXVI, pp. 241 - 258. [in Russian with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="2015">Sundukov (2015)</bibRefCitation>
newly recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" box="[640,963,1510,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zhelochovtsevi" subSpecies="nipponicus">
<emphasis box="[640,963,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. zhelochovtsevi nipponicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Kunashiri and Shikotan Islands and noted “Larvae on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Shinohara 1993)" baseAuthorityName="Shinohara" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[359,624,1546,1572]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[359,415,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Rosa</emphasis>
(Shinohara 1993)
</taxonomicName>
” (original in Russian). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" box="[895,1328,1546,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zhelochovtsevi" subSpecies="nipponicus">
<emphasis box="[895,1328,1546,1572]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Pamphilius zhelochovtsevi nipponicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded only from Honshu, not in Hokkaido, and the nominotypical subspecies is distributed in Primorskij Kraj and 
<collectingCountry box="[199,267,1619,1645]" name="South Korea" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Korea</collectingCountry>
(Shinohara 1993). The occurrence of this species (and subspecies) in southern Kuriles is not likely and needs confirmation. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[382,596,1654,1681]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="241 - 258" refId="ref79811" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2015) To the sawfly fauna (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of southern Kuriles. A. I. Kurentsov's Annual Memorial Meetings, Issue XXVI, pp. 241 - 258. [in Russian with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="2015">Sundukov’s (2015)</bibRefCitation>
host record is inexplicable and erroneous because Shinohara (1993) never mentioned the host plant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" box="[465,785,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zhelochovtsevi" subSpecies="nipponicus">
<emphasis box="[465,785,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. zhelochovtsevi nipponicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is still unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1437,1294,1897]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
Molecular data were available only for Japanese specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" box="[889,1207,1726,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zhelochovtsevi" subSpecies="nipponicus">
<emphasis box="[889,1207,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. zhelochovtsevi nipponicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(two COI sequences and one NaK sequence). In the COI analysis, the nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" box="[948,1264,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sulphureipes" subSpecies="sulphureipes">
<emphasis box="[948,1264,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. sulphureipes sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 3.4%, while in the NaK analysis, the nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kim" authorityYear="1963" box="[962,1091,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreanus">
<emphasis box="[962,1091,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. coreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the minimum distance of 1.5%. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1974" box="[224,522,1834,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhelochovtsevi">
<emphasis box="[224,522,1834,1860]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Pamphilius zhelochovtsevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[749,919,1834,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphureipes">
<emphasis box="[749,919,1834,1860]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (Shinohara 1993), which was retrieved as monophyletic with 100% UFBoot supports in our COI and NaK analyses (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1117,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 144" captionStartId="231.[151,250,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,187,1159]" captionTargetId="figure-19@231.[151,1436,181,1163]" captionTargetPageId="231" captionText="FIGURE 144. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sulphureipes group." pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Figs 144</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1129,1175,1870,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 158" captionStartId="243.[151,250,886,910]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,185,858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@243.[151,1436,181,862]" captionTargetPageId="243" captionText="FIGURE 158. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sulphureipes group." pageId="76" pageNumber="77">158</figureCitation>
).
